{
  "texts": [
    "Interfacing with iOS is more intricate, as there is no automated toolchain for controlling the device.",
    "To achieve this, we have built a Python-based service which maps commands like touch, swipe, and text input to a virtual Human Interface Device (HID), simulating a Bluetooth keyboard and mouse that controls the device.",
    "In both cases, the baseline power draw of Bluetooth and Wi-Fi events is subtracted from the energy traces.",
    "For the compilation and deployment of apps, we have a Mac Studio in the same network as the rest of PhoneLab, with remote access to the devices.",
    "Packages are installed through ADB and ideviceinstaller [60] for Android and iOS, respectively."
  ]
}